50:24.021 --> 50:27.257
Yeah. She asked why
the  Federales
were looking for us.

50:27.357 --> 50:31.194
I tell her you're my father,
and you broke out
of the  loco,

50:31.261 --> 50:32.896
the crazy hospital.

50:32.996 --> 50:35.599
And they're looking for you.

50:35.699 --> 50:37.768
And she bought into all that?

50:39.036 --> 50:40.937
She didn't believe me.

50:41.038 --> 50:43.440
So, then I told her

50:43.540 --> 50:46.043
you're here to bring me
to Texas with my father

50:46.109 --> 50:48.111
and my mother says no.

50:48.211 --> 50:50.347
So, you told her the truth.

50:51.381 --> 50:53.850
I thought
you didn't trust anyone.

50:54.885 --> 50:56.453
No.

50:56.553 --> 50:58.288
But you trust her?

51:01.558 --> 51:05.262
Yeah.
Yeah, for some reason,
I guess, yes.

51:06.863 --> 51:09.132
Oh, well,

51:09.232 --> 51:11.101
on that, I think we oughta...

51:11.935 --> 51:13.970
We oughta go.

51:14.071 --> 51:16.239
Will you, uh,
thank the  senora  for me?

51:17.307 --> 51:18.975
Senorita.

51:19.076 --> 51:22.045
She's not married.
She's a widow.

51:22.779 --> 51:24.748
Marta.

51:24.815 --> 51:26.416
Mi nombre,  name,

51:27.084 --> 51:28.218
Marta.

51:31.054 --> 51:32.255
I'm Mike.

51:33.156 --> 51:35.425
Si.  He say.

51:36.560 --> 51:37.561
Yeah.

51:39.396 --> 51:40.397
Okay.

52:20.203 --> 52:22.005
Not another roadblock.

52:37.287 --> 52:40.123
What's the Spanish word
for "irony"?

52:42.125 --> 52:45.295
Well, we'll have to go back
to that town we were in.

52:46.663 --> 52:49.833
Just wait till
this shitstorm's over with.

52:56.173 --> 52:58.642
Perfect place
to get out of the rain.

53:22.532 --> 53:23.533
Huh.

53:24.768 --> 53:26.269
It's a shrine, Mike.

53:32.108 --> 53:33.777
Of the  Virgen Maria.

53:50.894 --> 53:51.795
Okay.

53:51.895 --> 53:54.064
What are you doing?

53:54.130 --> 53:56.299
-Hmm?
-What are you doing?

53:56.399 --> 53:57.467
Oh, I'm, uh...

53:59.703 --> 54:01.471
I'm gonna go to sleep.

54:01.571 --> 54:03.473
What the hell
do you think this is?

54:03.573 --> 54:07.544
We cannot sleep in the shrine
of the  Virgen Maria.

54:07.611 --> 54:11.648
Maria's not gonna worry
about it. She's fine.

54:13.583 --> 54:15.318
She won't care.

54:26.463 --> 54:27.764
Night, kid.

54:32.902 --> 54:34.070
Mike?

54:34.137 --> 54:35.138
Yeah?

54:35.238 --> 54:37.073
Mike, do you believe in God?

54:41.511 --> 54:42.979
I don't know, kid.

54:44.247 --> 54:45.949
I guess so, yeah.

54:48.018 --> 54:51.254
You Catholic?

54:51.988 --> 54:53.323
No.

54:53.423 --> 54:55.425
I'm not Catholic, kid.

54:55.492 --> 54:57.794
That's too bad for you, Mike.

54:57.861 --> 55:00.196
Even if you believe in God
and you're not Catholic,

55:00.297 --> 55:03.833
they don't believe in you.

55:03.933 --> 55:07.470
What, is he playing favorites,
maybe, or something?

55:07.537 --> 55:09.205
Yeah.

55:09.306 --> 55:11.374
I don't believe this shit.

55:11.474 --> 55:14.511
"We're all God's children."

55:15.145 --> 55:16.179
Do you?

55:18.715 --> 55:22.152
Well, we're all
somebody's children, kid.

55:28.992 --> 55:31.027
Do you have any children?

55:32.662 --> 55:33.663
No.

55:36.666 --> 55:38.034
Oh, I did.

55:39.035 --> 55:40.036
Did?

55:40.970 --> 55:42.539
Yeah.

55:42.639 --> 55:44.240
Matthew, boy.

55:46.810 --> 55:49.145
My boy...

55:49.212 --> 55:51.848
and my wife were killed
in an auto accident

55:51.915 --> 55:53.516
some years back.

55:55.318 --> 55:56.319
Sorry.

55:59.756 --> 56:00.924
Anyway...

56:02.759 --> 56:06.096
I wasn't much good after that.

56:06.196 --> 56:08.431
I kind of went
on a rampage.

56:08.531 --> 56:10.266
Too much drinking.

56:11.167 --> 56:12.602
Being crazy.

56:16.373 --> 56:17.941
But your dad,

56:19.709 --> 56:21.511
he saved my ass.

56:23.546 --> 56:25.248
He gave me work.

56:27.684 --> 56:28.752
He...

56:30.186 --> 56:32.622
gave me my life back.

56:32.722 --> 56:34.457
I owe him a lot.

56:36.960 --> 56:39.629
And you're the payback, kid.

56:40.797 --> 56:42.298
You're the payback.

56:43.633 --> 56:45.602
I'm paying him back.

57:05.255 --> 57:06.256
Hey!

57:17.434 --> 57:19.602
Look at this. Fantastic, huh?

57:23.773 --> 57:25.742
How'd you know
we were here?

57:30.947 --> 57:34.851
She came to light a candle,
and she saw our car.

57:35.952 --> 57:36.986
Yeah.

57:37.921 --> 57:39.022
Well, thanks.

57:39.122 --> 57:40.423
Gracias.

57:42.492 --> 57:43.526
Muy bien.

58:07.817 --> 58:09.352
Oh, damn!

58:19.529 --> 58:20.897
What's the matter?

58:20.997 --> 58:22.465
Look, the car.

58:29.572 --> 58:31.341
Whoa, Jesus.

58:33.009 --> 58:34.511
Well,

58:34.577 --> 58:36.880
we better get used
to this town, kid.

58:36.980 --> 58:38.815
We're gonna be here
a while.

58:39.849 --> 58:41.684
It's a piece of shit.

59:01.604 --> 59:03.106
Everything all right?

59:03.206 --> 59:04.207
Hey.

59:05.708 --> 59:07.110
You speak English,  amigo?

59:07.210 --> 59:08.745
Yeah.

59:08.845 --> 59:12.782
These horse are for sale.
You want to buy?

59:12.882 --> 59:16.786
I noticed one of those guys
has got an injury

59:16.886 --> 59:18.888
on the left haunch there.

59:18.955 --> 59:20.590
He's a little rough to me.

59:20.690 --> 59:22.058
Yeah, in fact,
all your horses

59:22.125 --> 59:24.227
are a little
on the rough side.

59:24.294 --> 59:26.763
They get hurt
being rounded up.

59:26.863 --> 59:28.464
Wild horses, huh?

59:28.565 --> 59:31.467
Si,  we catch,
but not break them.

59:31.568 --> 59:33.303
They are very wild.

59:33.403 --> 59:35.071
Not many can ride.

59:35.138 --> 59:36.472
Yeah.

59:36.573 --> 59:39.576
Pretty hard to sell a horse
that you can't ride.

59:47.750 --> 59:50.153
Maybe we can do
something about that.

59:50.253 --> 59:52.221
-We? Who's we?
-Yeah.

59:52.288 --> 59:53.456
You and me.

59:54.591 --> 59:57.126
I don't even know how to ride.

59:57.226 --> 59:58.428
But I can do anything.

59:58.494 --> 59:59.762
Of course you can.

59:59.829 --> 1:00:01.798
Wouldn't want to
get up there in Texas

1:00:01.898 --> 1:00:04.934
and have people find out
you don't know how to ride.

1:00:34.197 --> 1:00:35.198
Whoa.

1:00:37.133 --> 1:00:38.334
Macho.

1:00:39.669 --> 1:00:41.037
Okay.

1:00:41.137 --> 1:00:43.006
Pick up the flow, will ya?

1:00:44.374 --> 1:00:46.709
Keep your weight
on the balls
of your feet.

1:00:50.346 --> 1:00:53.116
More like it.
Do less with your hands.

1:00:55.385 --> 1:00:56.853
Pick it up more.

1:00:58.388 --> 1:00:59.522
Attaboy.

1:01:01.057 --> 1:01:02.625
Not bad at all.

1:01:04.360 --> 1:01:06.896
Pick it up. Pick it up. More.

1:01:06.996 --> 1:01:08.297
There you go.

1:01:08.364 --> 1:01:10.900
Don't lay back.
Stay upright.

1:01:11.000 --> 1:01:13.336
There, that's good.
That's good.

1:01:13.403 --> 1:01:15.405
Heels down. That's good.

1:01:15.505 --> 1:01:16.739
That's a good
little figure eight.

1:01:16.839 --> 1:01:18.174
Come back this way.

1:01:23.546 --> 1:01:25.415
All right, son.
You're doing good.

1:01:25.515 --> 1:01:27.417
You're doing great.

1:01:27.517 --> 1:01:30.586
May not be a disgrace
in Texas after all.

1:01:56.079 --> 1:01:58.181
Here's a gift, ladies.

1:02:01.184 --> 1:02:02.418
Cafe?

1:02:04.053 --> 1:02:05.855
Sure. All right.

1:02:06.889 --> 1:02:09.258
-

1:02:09.358 --> 1:02:10.393
Okay.

1:02:24.207 --> 1:02:26.209
Thank you.

1:02:26.275 --> 1:02:31.380
You know,
we just brought you
that meat as a gift.

1:02:35.752 --> 1:02:37.987
Yeah, I just came here
to bring stuff.

1:02:38.087 --> 1:02:42.125
I didn't come here
to freeload a meal.

1:02:42.225 --> 1:02:43.326
Uh...

1:02:53.136 --> 1:02:57.106
Um, she says
she'll do as she pleases.

1:02:57.173 --> 1:02:58.775
Oh, all right.

1:03:00.109 --> 1:03:01.144
Okay.

1:03:14.524 --> 1:03:16.092
These your girls?

1:03:30.640 --> 1:03:31.841
Mm-mm.

1:03:31.941 --> 1:03:33.342
Granddaughters.

1:03:33.442 --> 1:03:36.779
Her daughter got sick
and died.

1:03:36.846 --> 1:03:38.447
Also her son-in-law.

1:03:39.816 --> 1:03:42.218
Her husband died too.

1:03:42.318 --> 1:03:44.554
Same illness. Two years ago.

1:03:44.654 --> 1:03:46.689
Now widow, like you.

1:03:48.057 --> 1:03:49.325
Sorry.

1:04:17.687 --> 1:04:19.222
She's deaf?

1:04:20.323 --> 1:04:21.490
Seems so.

1:04:23.392 --> 1:04:25.161
How do you know sign language?

1:04:26.696 --> 1:04:29.498
Just something you pick up
along the way.

1:04:44.513 --> 1:04:45.781
What did you say?

1:04:45.882 --> 1:04:47.917
Wouldn't you like to know?

1:06:06.295 --> 1:06:09.432
So, what's that all about?

1:06:10.333 --> 1:06:11.801
The deputy.

1:06:11.867 --> 1:06:13.302
What about the deputy?

1:06:13.369 --> 1:06:16.439
Uh, first,
he said he's a sheriff

1:06:16.505 --> 1:06:19.275
and it's his job to know
what's going on.

1:06:19.342 --> 1:06:22.278
But she said
he's not the sheriff.
He's a deputy.

1:06:22.345 --> 1:06:24.947
And that's only
because his uncle
made him deputy.

1:06:25.014 --> 1:06:27.350
And they don't even have
a police station.

1:06:27.450 --> 1:06:29.051
And if he didn't mind
his business,

1:06:29.151 --> 1:06:31.120
she said he never eat
at the  cantina  again.

1:06:38.995 --> 1:06:40.863
Uh, what's next?

1:06:54.043 --> 1:06:55.578
Looking good, kid.

1:06:58.247 --> 1:07:01.250
Look where you're going,
and go where you're looking.

1:07:03.019 --> 1:07:04.520
Good.

1:07:04.587 --> 1:07:06.188
Put your heels down.

1:07:06.255 --> 1:07:07.390
Okay.

1:07:07.490 --> 1:07:08.991
Heels down.

1:07:09.058 --> 1:07:11.260
Yeah, don't look like
a sack of potatoes there.

1:07:14.530 --> 1:07:17.266
Your dad's gonna be
a happy man
seeing you that way.

1:07:17.366 --> 1:07:18.567
-We'll see you in a bit.
- Yeah.

1:07:18.667 --> 1:07:21.504
Come on.
Come on. Come on.

1:07:26.008 --> 1:07:28.344
Uh, this is  Senora  Reyes.

1:07:28.411 --> 1:07:29.945
Her goat
was attacked by dogs,

1:07:30.046 --> 1:07:32.615
so I tell her
you're good with animals.

1:07:32.715 --> 1:07:34.517
Well, why don't you put him
over here.

1:07:34.583 --> 1:07:37.253
Put him on this table,
we'll take a look.

1:07:42.892 --> 1:07:44.727
Put him right up there.

1:07:45.594 --> 1:07:47.296
Let me see.

1:07:47.396 --> 1:07:49.565
Let's see. Oh, yeah.

1:07:49.632 --> 1:07:52.435
Yeah,
somebody chewed on him
pretty good.

1:07:52.535 --> 1:07:54.303
Not so good. Yeah.

1:07:56.439 --> 1:07:57.473
Yeah.

1:08:07.483 --> 1:08:10.319
Okay, I think
we can fix her up in a bit.

1:08:10.419 --> 1:08:11.620
And it's gonna be okay.

1:08:12.822 --> 1:08:14.156
All righty.

1:08:14.256 --> 1:08:15.491
Mike,
it should've taken three,

1:08:15.591 --> 1:08:16.959
maybe four days tops.

1:08:17.059 --> 1:08:19.161
But two goddamn weeks?
What are you doing?

1:08:19.261 --> 1:08:21.664
I told you
it was gonna
take a little while.

1:08:21.764 --> 1:08:23.332
I heard that already.

1:08:23.432 --> 1:08:25.768
Just keep telling him
what he wants to hear.

1:08:25.835 --> 1:08:27.303
-Who?
-  "Who?"

1:08:27.403 --> 1:08:30.072
The kid. Rafael.

1:08:30.973 --> 1:08:32.174
Just keep him happy,

1:08:32.274 --> 1:08:33.509
and whatever you do,

1:08:33.609 --> 1:08:35.177
do not let his mother
get a hold of him.

1:08:35.277 --> 1:08:37.613
Or her lawyers
will never respond.

1:08:37.680 --> 1:08:39.014
Respond to what?

1:08:39.115 --> 1:08:40.783
It's a business thing.

1:08:40.850 --> 1:08:42.351
A few years ago,
down there in Mexico,

1:08:42.451 --> 1:08:44.620
I invested in some property
in her name

1:08:44.687 --> 1:08:46.856
to avoid their goddamn taxes,

1:08:46.956 --> 1:08:49.625
and now those investments
have matured.

1:08:49.692 --> 1:08:51.861
So I want the return
on my investment.

1:08:51.961 --> 1:08:53.362
Just like the kid.

1:08:53.462 --> 1:08:55.431
Well, yeah, okay.
So, you get it.

1:08:55.498 --> 1:08:56.632
Mm-hmm.

1:08:56.699 --> 1:08:58.868
I get it.
You played me, you bastard.

1:08:58.968 --> 1:09:00.202
I didn't play you.

1:09:00.302 --> 1:09:02.538
What are you,
eight years old, Mike?

1:09:03.139 --> 1:09:04.173
Jesus!

1:09:04.273 --> 1:09:06.609
If I have something
she wants,

1:09:06.675 --> 1:09:08.777
maybe she'll negotiate.

1:09:08.844 --> 1:09:11.180
Christ, I'm a reasonable man.

1:09:11.280 --> 1:09:13.549
I'm just asking for my half.

1:09:13.649 --> 1:09:16.385
This kid would be better off
without either one of you.

1:09:16.485 --> 1:09:17.820
Well, you know what?

1:09:17.887 --> 1:09:19.221
It doesn't make a shit
what you think, Mike.

1:09:19.321 --> 1:09:21.056
I'm his father

1:09:21.157 --> 1:09:23.959
and I actually
want him back.

1:09:24.026 --> 1:09:27.796
This isn't all about
the money, okay?

1:09:27.863 --> 1:09:29.465
The kid's my son.

1:09:30.499 --> 1:09:31.867
So, please...

1:09:33.068 --> 1:09:35.738
Please, can you stick
to the plan?

1:09:35.838 --> 1:09:37.706
Just meet me at the border
with him.

1:09:39.408 --> 1:09:40.409
Yeah.

1:09:55.724 --> 1:09:56.892
Was that my father?

1:09:56.992 --> 1:09:58.260
Yeah, it was, kid.

1:09:58.360 --> 1:09:59.995
Did he say anything
about me?

1:10:00.062 --> 1:10:01.597
Ask how I am?

1:10:01.697 --> 1:10:05.000
Well, he did, yeah. He...
He wants the best for ya.

1:10:05.067 --> 1:10:07.269
-He does?
- Yeah.

1:10:07.369 --> 1:10:09.838
He still wants me?
He still wants me to come?

1:10:09.905 --> 1:10:12.241
'Course he does, kid.
Why wouldn't he?

1:10:17.346 --> 1:10:19.615
Hold it, hold it, hold it.
Give me that.

1:10:20.716 --> 1:10:23.118
Okay, come on, there.

1:10:23.219 --> 1:10:24.520
Right through there.

1:10:24.587 --> 1:10:27.356
Stick your head in there,
and put it on up here.

1:10:28.557 --> 1:10:30.726
Put this here. Okay.

1:10:31.894 --> 1:10:33.028
We got him.

1:10:33.095 --> 1:10:35.698
Now, that was the easy part.

1:10:35.764 --> 1:10:38.033
-That was the easy part?
- Yeah.

1:10:38.100 --> 1:10:41.136
Next, they don't like it
when you cinch the girth.

1:10:42.137 --> 1:10:43.572
It's just like this.

1:10:43.639 --> 1:10:45.608
You just have to pull,
cinch it up.

1:10:45.708 --> 1:10:46.809
You can do it.

1:10:46.909 --> 1:10:48.477
-You wanna try it?
- Okay.

1:10:48.577 --> 1:10:51.647
Just cinch it up,
and put up half of...
An eighth of it.

1:10:53.048 --> 1:10:55.651
- Whoa! Whoa.

1:10:57.419 --> 1:10:58.654
Whoa.

1:10:58.754 --> 1:11:00.422
Whoa! He's so wild.

1:11:00.489 --> 1:11:03.058
Okay, yeah.
Take it easy.

1:11:03.125 --> 1:11:04.893
Hey, hey. Hey.

1:11:13.269 --> 1:11:14.837
How did you do that?

1:11:15.638 --> 1:11:17.573
We did it, partner.

1:11:17.640 --> 1:11:18.841
We did it.

1:11:39.194 --> 1:11:40.296
Buenos dias.

1:11:40.362 --> 1:11:41.297
Buenos dias.

1:11:41.363 --> 1:11:42.531
Sleep well?

1:11:42.631 --> 1:11:44.700
I did, yeah. I did.

1:11:44.800 --> 1:11:45.801
Thank you.

1:11:55.110 --> 1:11:59.381
Uh, Marta says
we can stay in the  casita
behind her house

1:11:59.481 --> 1:12:00.949
while we are here.

1:12:01.483 --> 1:12:02.885
No.

1:12:02.985 --> 1:12:04.720
We can't do that.
Can't do that.

1:12:04.820 --> 1:12:07.189
We've already
imposed on her enough.

1:12:07.289 --> 1:12:08.290
Well...

1:12:25.307 --> 1:12:26.408
Uh...

1:12:26.508 --> 1:12:27.576
She said it's her choice.

1:12:27.676 --> 1:12:29.011
-And she already...
-Right.

1:12:29.078 --> 1:12:30.312
...cleaned it out for us.

1:12:30.379 --> 1:12:32.014
Plus, she says
we can't keep sleeping

1:12:32.081 --> 1:12:33.916
in the shrine
of the  Virgen Maria.

1:12:34.016 --> 1:12:36.418
It's not a hotel.

1:12:36.518 --> 1:12:39.888
I know.
I'm fighting a losing battle.

1:12:41.657 --> 1:12:42.925
Okay.

1:12:43.025 --> 1:12:44.593
It's good or it's no?

1:12:45.494 --> 1:12:46.829
It's no.

1:12:48.030 --> 1:12:49.932
But what do we do
when we leave?

1:12:50.032 --> 1:12:53.402
We get ourselves another car,
that's what we do.

1:13:31.907 --> 1:13:33.208
Cook?

1:13:33.275 --> 1:13:34.943
Yeah. Well, you're always
cooking all the time.

1:13:35.043 --> 1:13:36.578
I thought
I would do it for you.

1:13:36.645 --> 1:13:39.214
-And cowboys always cook.

1:13:39.281 --> 1:13:40.983
It's kind of our deal.

1:13:45.721 --> 1:13:46.889
Okay.

1:13:48.290 --> 1:13:49.324
You want?

1:13:49.425 --> 1:13:50.826
-Um...

1:13:50.926 --> 1:13:51.927
Yeah.

1:14:09.011 --> 1:14:10.012
Amen.

1:14:15.250 --> 1:14:16.418
Okay.

1:14:20.456 --> 1:14:21.356
Um...

1:14:21.457 --> 1:14:23.792
I think she likes you.

1:14:25.194 --> 1:14:28.630
Just keep
your big mouth shut.

1:14:28.697 --> 1:14:32.100
-And I think you like her.

1:14:49.885 --> 1:14:51.787
-Gracias.
-Gracias.

1:14:57.860 --> 1:14:59.561
More money to come.

1:14:59.661 --> 1:15:01.163
More mustangs to break.

